---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for MyTattoo.Software. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
>
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <div class="bg-gray-100 py-3">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'Privacy Policy' }
      ]} />
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

        <p class="text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: July 2026</p>

        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          MyTattoo.Software ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website mytattoo.software or use our tattoo booking software.
        </p>

        {/* Draft 2026-07, grounded in the app data model & dependencies, pending legal review — not legal advice. Open items: back the processor relationship with a DPA; confirm each provider's legal entity and the database host; verify Stripe merchant-of-record / chargeback position; confirm lawful-basis mapping and transfer safeguards. */}
        <h2>Our Role in Your Data</h2>
        <p>MyTattoo.Software (a service of LEAVE.REVIEW LTD) has two different roles under data protection law, depending on whose information is involved:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Artists.</strong> For the information we hold about you as an artist — your account, business profile, and how you use the service — we are the <strong>data controller</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>Your clients.</strong> For the information about your clients that you collect through MyTattoo — their name, contact details, booking and intake responses, and any reference images they upload — <strong>you (the artist) are the data controller and we act as your data processor</strong>, handling that information on your instructions only to provide the booking service. You are responsible for having a lawful basis for that data and for giving your clients appropriate privacy information (and obtaining their consent where required).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, and business details when you register for our service.</li>
          <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Information you provide when contacting us via forms or email.</li>
          <li><strong>Client Data:</strong> Information about your clients that you input into our software, including names, contact details, appointment history, and reference images they submit at booking.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Billing details processed through our secure payment providers.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Reference images.</strong> Clients can upload up to five reference images when they request a booking, stored securely with our hosting provider. Please upload only images relevant to the tattoo — a reference image can sometimes reveal sensitive information (for example an existing tattoo, a scar, or the part of the body involved), so avoid uploading anything that isn't needed for the booking.
        </p>

        <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, features used, and interactions with our software.</li>
          <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Browser type, operating system, and device identifiers.</li>
          <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> IP addresses, access times, and referring URLs.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide and maintain our tattoo booking software</li>
          <li>Process transactions and send related information</li>
          <li>Send administrative information, updates, and security alerts</li>
          <li>Respond to your comments, questions, and customer service requests</li>
          <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve our services</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Legal Bases for Processing (UK GDPR)</h2>
        <p>Where we are the controller (artist data), we rely on the following legal bases:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>To provide the service</strong> — your account, bookings, payments, and service emails: performance of our contract with you.</li>
          <li><strong>To keep the service secure and improve it</strong> — logs, rate-limiting, and aggregate usage: our legitimate interests in running a safe, reliable service.</li>
          <li><strong>Website analytics</strong> — your consent, given through our cookie banner.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal and tax obligations</strong> — compliance with a legal obligation.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For your clients' information, you (the artist) are the controller and are responsible for the lawful basis on which their data is collected and used.</p>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your personal information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes encryption, secure servers, and regular security assessments.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal information we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
          <li>Request data portability</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at privacy@mytattoo.software. If you are in the UK and we haven't resolved your concern, you have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>. If your query is about client data held by an artist, please contact that artist, who is the controller of that information.
        </p>

        <h2>Service Providers (Sub-processors)</h2>
        <p>We rely on a small number of trusted providers to run MyTattoo. Each processes personal data only as needed to provide its part of the service, under its own privacy terms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing. Client deposits are handled by Stripe and paid to the artist's own connected Stripe account.</li>
          <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting for our website and app, and secure storage for client reference images.</li>
          <li><strong>Resend</strong> — sending booking notifications and sign-in emails.</li>
          <li><strong>Upstash</strong> — rate-limiting infrastructure that processes IP addresses to protect the service from abuse.</li>
          <li><strong>Our managed database provider</strong> — stores your account and booking data.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — website usage analytics, loaded only if you accept analytics cookies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Some of our providers are based outside the UK or process data in other countries, including the United States. Where personal data is transferred outside the UK, we rely on appropriate safeguards — such as a UK adequacy decision or the UK Addendum to the EU Standard Contractual Clauses — so that your information stays protected.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>

        <h3>What are cookies?</h3>
        <p>
          A cookie is a small file containing a string of characters that is sent to your computer when you visit a website. When you visit the website again, the cookie allows that website to recognize your browser or device. Cookies may store unique identifiers, user preferences and other information.
        </p>

        <h3>Cookie Consent Management</h3>
        <p>
          When you first visit our Site, you will be presented with a cookie consent banner that allows you to accept or decline non-essential cookies.
        </p>

        <p><strong>If you accept cookies:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>We will use Google Analytics to collect anonymized usage data to help us improve the Site</li>
          <li>Analytics cookies will be set on your device</li>
          <li>Your consent choice is stored in your browser's local storage</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>If you decline cookies:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>No analytics cookies will be set</li>
          <li>Google Analytics will not be loaded or activated</li>
          <li>Only essential cookies necessary for the Site to function will be used</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          You can change your cookie preferences at any time by clearing your browser's local storage and refreshing the page, which will show the consent banner again.
        </p>

        <h3>Google Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google LLC ("Google"). Google Analytics uses cookies to help us analyze how users interact with our Site. The information generated by the cookie about your use of the Site (including your IP address) is transmitted to and stored by Google. Google will use this information for the purpose of evaluating your use of the Site, compiling reports on website activity for us, and providing other services relating to website activity and internet usage.
        </p>

        <p><strong>To opt out of Google Analytics, you can:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use our cookie consent banner to decline cookies</li>
          <li>Install the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on: <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a></li>
          <li>Clear your cookies and decline when the banner reappears</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
        <p><strong>Necessary Cookies:</strong> These cookies are necessary for you to browse the Site and use its features. Without these cookies, certain aspects of the Site may not be available to you.</p>
        <p><strong>Analytics Cookies (with your consent):</strong> These cookies collect information about how you use the Site, such as which pages you visit, the time you spend on the Site, and which links you click. These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with the Site. All information collected is aggregated and does not identify you personally.</p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our service is not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: privacy@mytattoo.software</li>
          <li>Website: <a href="/contact/">Contact Form</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Company Information</h2>
        <p>
          MyTattoo.Software is a trading name of LEAVE.REVIEW LTD, a company registered in England and Wales.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Company Number: 05408918</li>
          <li>Registered Office: 124 City Road, London, EC1V 2NX, United Kingdom</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
